main event: Mr. and Mrs. A.A. McKim reported seeing an unidentified aerial object over Franklin, Ohio on May 22, 1964 from 7:00 PM to 7:15 PM.
interesting points: The object was observed for 2 minutes and 30 seconds.
The object appeared solid and brighter than the brightest stars.
The object was described as a bright light moving at a very high rate of speed.
The object was tracked on radar for over 10 minutes before being lost.
The object was initially reported to Capt. Smith as a very bright light, but was later identified as the Echo II satellite.
photographs: yes, the report indicates photographs were taken
